This is the second of a class of bugs of the same form that we call the heart of darkness. They're all of the same basic form, doing something dodgy inside of an IO completion callback. We have disabled all asynchronous FileStream code as a workaround.

src/System.Private.CoreLib/shared/System/IO/FileStreamCompletionSource.Win32.cs: 189:
````
                        Exception e = Win32Marshal.GetExceptionForWin32Error(errorCode);
                        e.SetCurrentStackTrace();
                        TrySetException(e);
````

Should clearly read:
````
                        try {
                            Exception e = Win32Marshal.GetExceptionForWin32Error(errorCode);
                            e.SetCurrentStackTrace();
                            TrySetException(e);
                        } catch (Exception e2)
                        {
                            TrySetException(e2);
                        }
````

This time around, no equivalent bug exits on the Unix side because Unix doesn't provide async read/write on local disks.

